cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DL 

The paper focuses on literature-based knowledge discovery using keyword co-occurrence networks and LSTM networks. This falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of LSTM networks for predicting future connections among knowledge units suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). Additionally, the study uses bibliometrics and temporal analysis, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
